No strings attached, we just want to bless you!

The softball players, junior high and high school, are welcome to start practicing from 2:30 until 4:30. Extra time is available for any players who are willing to show up early or stay late. Thank You,
Jeremy Williams

The state of Oklahoma requires that all incoming 7th graders receive their TDap immunization before the first day of school. We will need a copy of up-to-date shot records for your students. More information about immunization requirements is available from the Oklahoma State Department of Health.

https://www.ok.gov/health2/documents/IMM_Parents_School_Vaccines_Requirements_OK_English.pdf



Thank you!

Audra Broadhead

post_text:
Greetings, Tiger Nation.

2020-2021 enrollment will begin on Tuesday, July 28th.

Returning Students: Log into teacherease.com.
Complete the online registration. Go to libertyps.org and complete the remaining forms. Email the forms to your building secretary. You may also drop off the paper forms to the correct building during office hours.

New Students: Pick up a packet from the correct building. Bring a copy of birth certificate, shot records, and evidence of proof of residency. The completed packet can be returned during office hours.

Students with No internet access: Pick up a paper packet from the correct building. Complete the packet and return it during office hours.

We are looking forward to a successful year.

Office hours 7/28-7/31
Tuesday, Wednesday, Friday 9-3
Thursday 12-7

Good Afternoon Liberty Folks,

Tomorrow, Thursday June 25th, is our last food distribution of the summer. We will have our usual Child Nutrition feeding as well as the fresh produce distributed by our friends at Bixby Freewill Baptist. Our summer athletes will be joining in to help unload since we were overwhelmed with the amount of food coming straight from the farm. Everybody is invited to participate so please come out to say thanks to all of those who have made such great efforts to make sure Liberty got fed. The times are 9am to 10am but please note that due to construction you may need to enter and exit from the high school side.

==================================
Phillip Garland
Liberty Public Schools
Mounds, OK 74047
phone: 918-366-8496
email: phillip.garland@libertyps.org

post_text:
Liberty Graduation Procedures

All graduates will arrive at New Beginnings at 6 p.m.

Students will be sitting in a social distance setting.

Families will be staggered alphabetically.

There will be a sign in sheet for all attendees.

Each student will be allowed ten entries.

We will ask families to enter as groups. We will sit families as follows:

A through I from 6 to 6:10
J through R from 6:10 -6:20
S through Z from 6:20-6:30

We encourage the use of masks and ask that social distancing be practiced.

The graduation ceremony will begin at 7.

A spot will be designated for families to photograph their senior as they cross the stage. Details will be given at the Graduation.

Questions you may have

No tickets

We will not provide a photographer and all photographs will be taken outside.

We will video and put the video on youtube.

Seats will be labeled and placed with the number of seats requested by the graduate.
Meaning your family will not be socially distanced.

We will try to space families to allow for social distancing.

Thank You,
Jeremy Williams

post_text:
Greetings all,

Unfortunately the group that had been working with the schools to provide weekly food security for families on Mondays has ended but our summer feeding program begins Thursday, May 14th.

We will be distributing a weeks worth of breakfasts and lunches for ALL children 0-18 every Thursday through June. This is not restricted to anyone including students from other districts. We will be able to continue this program as long as we can feed at least 50 children; if our demand falls below that we will have to discontinue the program.

We are extremely grateful to all the volunteers and workers who have gotten us this far. Please consider participating in our summer feeding program and have a good evening.

Sincerely,

Phillip Garland, EdD

post_text:
Good Afternoon Tigers,

I hope your day is ending on a good note. The Liberty Schools Fencing Advisory Committee met last night and had a productive first round of discussions. As a first step in getting our campus looking and working well we need to remove the old fence and I have a proposition to community members but please understand that further action may require Board approval. If anyone is interested or knows of an interested party who would want to remove our current fencing for repurposing or recycling, please email Phillip.garland@libertyps.org with your contact details. Plan B would be to find someone who is interested in repurposing or recycling the materials but cant uninstall the fence themselves please respond to this email.

Obviously if we find someone to remove the fence then we can put more effort and finances toward our total project of beautifying, securing, and enhancing our schools grounds and parking areas. Please ask around to see if this could be a win-win for the taker and the district. Thank you for your attention.

Regards,

Phillip Garland, EdD

Foundations of Manufacturing Tech students! Tune in this evening! The Liberty Chapter will be recognized! Just follow the link!
Please share this information with your students so they can join in on the SkillsUSA Oklahoma Virtual Celebration and Awards Event tomorrow, Friday, April 24th at 7 p.m.!
Dozens of award winners will be recognized, district officers recognized and we will also be announcing who will be serving on the 2020-21 state officer team.
The state officer team will be leading this live event that will be broadcast on the Facebook
https://www.facebook.com/SkillsUSAOklahoma/live/
and the
SkillsUSA OK YouTube Channel https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEGSW42Dc-C9Qay_2yoXX1A
THREE VERY SPECIAL GUEST SCHEDULED TO JOIN US LIVE!
Oklahoma Governor Kevin Stitt
SkillsUSA National Executive Director Chelle Travis
NTHS Executive Director Peyton Holland
Hope you join the State Officer Team and the Governor of the Great State of Oklahoma as we celebrate this record breaking year for SkillsUSA and most importantly celebrate our students.

Good evening, Tiger Nation. The Staff and Administration are here to support you during this time of distance learning. This is a new experience for all of us, and as such, we want to focus on each other's well-being as a priority while we are learning. Please extend grace to all as we navigate these new experiences and learn together. Below you will find some information regarding contacting the school while the buildings are closed.

Main offices:

Elementary (PK-3rd grades) 918-366-8311
Middle School (4-6th grades) 918-366-1500
Jr High/High School (7-12th grades) 918-366-8784
Superintendent's office 918-366-8496

To reach Principals/Staff directly, dial 918-366-8496. When the recording begins, dial the correct extension:
Mr. Williams ext 133
Mrs. Stewart ext 112
Mrs. Evans ext 109
Mrs. Howard ext 160

Parents and guardians of 20/20 Seniors don't forget to submit 4 to 5 baby pictures for the 20/20 Liberty Yearbook, the DEADLINE for SENIOR BABY PICTURES is JANUARY 22. Also, the DEADLINE for SENIOR ADs is FEBRUARY 1. If you would like to purchase a SENIOR AD, they are $35 for a quarter page. You will want to submit 1 or 2 pictures of your seniors (preferably one being a senior picture) and your personal message. All payments for Senior ads are to be made to Mrs. Rodgers (linda.rodgers@libertyps.org) at the high school. You will also want to drop off your pictures and text copy to Mrs. Rodgers by email or in person.

Finally, if you have not ordered your 2020 Liberty Schools Yearbook, don't wait. Yearbooks will only be available online until February 1st, so order soon! You can order your yearbook at https://ybpay.lifetouch.com and the Yearbook ID: 13976620.

If you have questions, please contact Mrs. Rodgers by email at linda.rodgers@libertyps.org

January 7, 2020

Important Notice to all Students Riding Bus #2 AM Route

Due to a shortage of bus drivers, in the near future there may be a change in the timing of bus #2s AM route. It is possible that this route will need to run approximately 20 minutes later. If this situation does arise, you will be notified as far in advance as possible.
Please make sure that the school has current contact information that would allow us to send an all-call if needed. Information will also be posted on the schools Facebook page.
**At this time there is no change. However, we wanted families to be able to plan for this possible change.

Thank you for your understanding in this matter.

Liberty Public Schools

post_text: The Liberty administration was made aware this morning of a potential threat that had been posted on social media. Law enforcement was notified, and the administrators and staff were vigilant in supervision of the campus. Through the investigation, we have discovered the individual who made the post and have ascertained that was intended as a joke. Any such threats will always be taken seriously. Thankfully, this situation has been resolved. Liberty Public Schools will always place the safety of students and staff as the highest priority.

Through the investigation, we have discovered the individual who made the post and have ascertained that it was intended as a joke. Any such threat will always be taken seriously. Thankfully, this situation has been resolved. Liberty Public Schools will always place the safety of students and staff as the highest priority.

post_text:
Elementary pre-Christmas performances have been scheduled during school hours for Pre-K through Grade 3 . The performances will be December 13, 2019 with Pre-K and KG at 1:45-2:15 and Grade 1-3 at 2:45-3:15.

Some parents have voiced concerns that this change makes it difficult for parents and grandparents to attend because of their work schedules. There are reasons behind the change from night time performances to the school day: In December there are very few evenings without a conflict with scheduled basketball games; historically it has been problematic to get all of the students to attend in the evening; and pre-K and KG performances have been held during the day previously and the daytime performance allows parents with younger and older elementary students to see them at one time.

We hope that advanced notice of over a month will enable all parents and families to participate in their children's celebrations.

Due to the tragic loss of one of our students, there will be several counselors, along with Mrs. Broadhead, available to speak to students and staff as needed on Tuesday, October 22, 2019. Liberty Public Schools will not be in session on Friday, October 25th, due to the funeral which will be at 10 AM in the High School gym that day. Our students' needs are our top priority as we move forward in processing and grieving. Additional support will be provided this week as needed. Thank you for your support and prayers. The makeup day will be the first planned snow day, December 9th.
#Weareliberty

Important information regarding gate prices and rules.

Adult admission will remain $5 for adults and $3 for 7-12 students for varsity games. Admission for JH games will be $3 for adults and $2 for 7-12 students.

Students in grades PK-6 will be admitted FREE to all games, if accompanied by an adult.

Students in grades PK-6 will not be admitted without an adult.

We will offer a Senior admission fee of $3 for HS games, and $2 for JH games.

Season passes are on sale in the athletic office. A pass will entitle the bearer admission to all VARSITY (not JH) sports events for the 2019-2020 school year. Cost is $50 for adults, and $35 for students. We have 5 home football games and 8 home basketball games.
This pass will also include Varsity baseball and softball.

Driver Education Class- 2019 Summer Course

Liberty High School is offering Driver Education classes again this year. Class will begin May 28th2019, 8am to 4pm Tuesday- Friday. Students are required to complete 30 hours of classroom instruction before they are able to schedule driving with the instructor.
There are only 12 available openings this year, and payment must be made to guarantee your students enrollment. Payment can be made to Liberty Public Schools through the H.S. front office. Cost of Drivers Ed. is $200.00.

If you have any questions, please contact Leslie Romine at 918-366-8784.

post_text: This year we are going to give physicals on May 6, 2019. All students who participate in athletics in the 2019-20 school year must have a current physical on file, and that physical must be dated after 5/1/19. Physicals will be in the HS Gym, beginning at 4 PM. Cost is $20. Bryan Dunn, our certified trainer, will conduct the preliminary checklist ( height, weight, BP, etc.) This will completed in the various JH and HS sports before May 6. All elementary and middle school students who need a physical should plan to be here on May 6. This is an excellent opportunity to get student physicals completed early. Knox Labs will also be here on that date to do baseline drug testing for the 2019-20 school year. Cost is $20, and this is required for all extracurricular activities. There will be NO SCHOOL PHYSICALS IN THE FALL. If students do not get their physical on May5, they will be responsible for obtaining a physical before sports begin in the fall. Checks for physicals should be to Brothers Medical. Checks for drug test should be made out to Liberty PS.
